               <scopecontent id="aspace_bc917723dc06437e58dde2564d482f9d">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Includes bookplates of the following individuals: Rev. Edwin A. Dalrymple, D.D., Charles H. Ferris, Grace Hopper, Catharine and Stanley Miller, Robert V. New, The Oldens, John Quinn, Francis Waring Robinson.</p>
                  <p>Grace Hopper plate included the following note by Lowenstein: "Grace Hopper, a U.S. Navy Officer, was also a computer pioneer, hence the zeros and ones. This may be her bookplate."</p>
                  <p>Francis Waring Robinson plate included the following note by Lowenstein: "Robinson was a curator at the Detroit Institute of Art. (1907-1985)"</p>
                  <p>Also includes bookplates of the following institutions: Alpha Delta Phi (Cornell Chapter) [2 versions], Boys High School Brooklyn, Hampton Library-Bridgehampton, NY, Norwalk Public Library, Pequot Library, South Norwalk Public Library, Treadwell Library-Massachusetts General Hospital, and Westport Public Library.</p>
               </scopecontent>
